25|$|Deep Space Climate Observatory (DSCOVR), {{launched}} on 11 February 2015, began orbiting L1 on 8 June 2015 {{to study the}} solar wind {{and its effects on}} Earth. DSCOVR is unofficially known as GORESAT, because it carries a camera always oriented to Earth and capturing full-frame photos of the planet similar to the Blue Marble. This concept was proposed by then-Vice President of the United States Al Gore in 1998 and was a centerpiece in his film <b>An</b> <b>Inconvenient</b> <b>Truth.</b>|$|E
